cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on visual inspection of leather surfaces and utilizes handcrafted feature extractors and data-driven methods for representation of leather patches. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses multiple classifiers, including artificial neural networks, for leather defect classification. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper utilizes machine learning techniques for automatic leather defect classification. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image processing and analysis of leather surfaces. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves the classification of leather defects, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval from visual data.
